General.Name: Santana Minerals Ltd
General.Description: Santana Minerals Limited engages in the exploration and evaluation of gold, silver, and base metal properties in New Zealand, Cambodia, and Mexico. It holds a 100% interest in the Bendigo-Ophir gold project covering an area of 292 square kilometers located in Central Otago, New Zealand. The company also holds interests in the Cuitaboca Silver-Gold Project that covers an area of 5,500 ha situated in Mexico; and two gold exploration licenses in Cambodia. Santana Minerals Limited was incorporated in 2013 and is based in Brisbane, Australia.
